&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 2 Clerical Officer&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An opportunity has arisen within the Radiology Clinical Service Unit for a highly motivated and enthusiastic person to join the team as a Clerical Officer. We are looking for someone who is flexible (37.5 hours) and willing to cover a 7 day week rota which would also include evening and weekend shifts.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This would be an ideal opportunity for someone looking to expand their experience and knowledge.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidate will provide a comprehensive administrative/clerical and reception service to the Radiology department in line with Trust departmental guidance and polices.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Candidates will need excellent communication skills, the ability to work as part of a team and organise/prioritise their own workload.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidate will be the first point of contact for patients and visitors to the department, an NVQ 2 in customer care or equivalent would therefore be desirable but not essential.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We will in turn offer support through a structured period of induction and training along with opportunities for professional development in a supportive environment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Previous applicants need not apply.&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
